# React + TypeScript + Bun Stack

## Package Manager

Always use Bun commands:

- Install: `bun add [package]`
- Dev server: `bun dev`
- Build: `bun run build`
- Remove: `bun remove [package]`

## TypeScript Standards

- Enable strict mode
- Define interfaces for all props and state
- Use type inference where possible
- Avoid `any` type; use `unknown` if needed

## Project Structure

```
src/
├── components/   # Reusable UI components
├── pages/        # Page-level components
├── hooks/        # Custom React hooks
├── types/        # TypeScript type definitions
├── utils/        # Helper functions
├── api/          # API integration layer
└── styles/       # Global styles and themes
```

## Environment Variables

- Store in `.env.local` for local development
- Use `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix only for values safe to expose in the browser bundle
- Keep secrets server-only: `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`, `GEMINI_API_KEY`, `APP_BASIC_AUTH_*`
- Never commit `.env.local` to version control
- Document all required variables in `.env.example`
